ALTER-->By using this alter command to modify the structure of an existing database object.

DROP-->By using this command we can drop existing database object or table permanently.
TRUNCATE--> By using this command to delete all rows present in a table.
RENAME-->It is used to rename the table names or column names etc...

DML(Data Manipulation Language)
INSERT--> By using this command they can insert some into a table.
UPDATE-->By using this command we can update the existing records based on some conditions.
DELETE-->By using this command we can delete the existing table records based on some conditions.
LOCK-->It can be used to control access to a resource ensuring the only one transaction can access it at a time of preventing conflicts.
DCL(Data Control Language)
GRANT-->This command is used to give specific permission to a user in database this permission might be include the ability to select or update or delete data as we as create or drop tables.
REVOKE--> This command is used to take away granted permission from the user.
TCL(Transaction Control Language)
COMMIT-->This command is used to permanently save the changes made during the current transaction. once transaction is committed it changes became permanent and visible to other transactions.
ROLLBACK--> if an error occurs or if transaction needs to be canceled for any reason rollback is issued to revert the database.
in simple it is used to undo operations changes made during the current transactions.
SAVEPOINT-->It is used to set a point within a transaction who which you can later rollback.
DQL(Data Query Language)
SELECT-->This command is used to retrieve data from one or more tables in a database.

