Data Types in SQL (MySQL)
-----------------------------------
INT ->
NUMERIC ->
CHAR -> Fixed-length string.
Example: Gender ('M', 'F').
VARCHAR –> Variable-length string.
Example: Name ('Ravi', 'Girisha').
TEXT –> Stores large text data (up to 65,535 characters).
Example: Comments, descriptions.
TINYTEXT –> Small text data (up to 255 characters).
Example: Short notes.
MEDIUMTEXT –> Medium-sized text data (up to 16 million characters).
Example: Articles, blogs.
LONGTEXT –> Very large text data (up to 4 GB).
Example: Books, large documents.
ENUM –> Stores one value from a predefined list.
Example: ENUM('Male','Female','Other').
SET –> Multiple values from a list


